As of the 2010 census, there were 171 people living in the CDP: 83 male and 88 female. 66 were 19 years old or younger, 28 were ages 20–34, 33 were between the ages of 35 and 49, 29 were between 50 and 64, and the remaining 15 were aged 65 and above. The median age was 31.1 years.

The racial makeup of the CDP was 54.4% [[White Americans|White]], 5.8% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2.3% [[Native Americans in the United States|American Indian]], 0.6% [[African Americans|Black or African American]], 26.9% [[Race (United States Census)|Other]], and 9.9% [[Race (United States Census)|two or more races]]. 78.4% of the population were [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race.

There were 42 households in the CDP, 38 family households (90.5%) and 4 non-family households (9.5%), with an average household size of 4.07. Of the family households, 33 were married couples living together, with 1 single father and 4 single mothers; while the non-family households included 3 adults living alone: 2 male and 1 female.

The CDP contained 46 housing units, of which 42 were occupied and 4 were vacant.<ref name="GR2">{{Cite web |title=American FactFinder: Padre Ranchitos CDP, Arizona |url=https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0451800 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://archive.today/20200213094735/https://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US0451800 |archive-date=February 13, 2020 |access-date=January 7, 2017 |publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]}}</ref>

